  {
    "instruction": "A humanoid robot stumbled over a small stone while walking on a flat floor. Use the xxGemma DSL. First import tensor and robot1. Available functions: robot1_normal_act() -> tensor (starts the walking motion), robot1_error_router_determine() -> str (returns the recovery policy), robot1_walk_error_recovery() -> tensor (generates a recovery motion), robot1_error_router_reinforce(tensor) -> None (updates the router using a recovery loss tensor), robot1_unhandlable_error() -> str (reports an unrecoverable fault). Recover the robot safely without reinforcement.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$motion = tensor robot1_normal_act()\n[EXCEPTION]Robot lost balance.\n[COMMENT]A small stumble on a flat floor should use the walking recovery policy.\n[CODE]show robot1_error_router_determine()\n[RESULT]walking\n[CODE]$recovery = tensor robot1_walk_error_recovery()\nThe robot recovered from a small stumble on the flat floor.\n[CODE]return \"Recovered\"",
