  {
    "instruction": "A robot failed to grasp a slippery plastic bottle. Use the xxGemma DSL. First import tensor and robot1. Available functions: robot1_scan() -> tensor (captures sensor data), robot1_is_normal(tensor) -> bool (checks whether the scan is valid), robot1_model(tensor) -> tensor (generates a grasp model), robot1_act(tensor) -> str (executes the grasp), robot1_error_router_determine() -> str (selects a recovery strategy), robot1_grasp_error_recovery() -> tensor (generates a new grasp motion), robot1_error_router_reinforce(tensor) -> None (updates the router), robot1_unhandlable_error() -> str (reports a fatal error). Recover by switching to a torque-oriented grasp policy without reinforcement.",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$scan = tensor robot1_scan()\n[CODE]$plan = tensor robot1_model($scan)\n[CODE]robot1_act($plan)\n[EXCEPTION]robot1_exception: Grasp failed.\n[COMMENT]A slippery bottle should switch to the torque recovery policy.\n[CODE]show robot1_error_router_determine()\n[RESULT]torque\n[CODE]$recovery = tensor robot1_grasp_error_recovery()\nThe robot successfully grasped the slippery bottle after changing the grasp policy.\n[CODE]return \"Recovered\"",
