  {
    "instruction": "A warehouse robot failed to hold a heavy metal component because it slipped during lifting. Use the xxGemma DSL. First import tensor and robot1. Available functions: robot1_scan() -> tensor (captures sensor data), robot1_is_normal(tensor) -> bool (checks sensor validity), robot1_model(tensor) -> tensor (builds a grasp model), robot1_act(tensor) -> str (executes the grasp), robot1_error_router_determine() -> str (selects the recovery strategy), robot1_grasp_error_recovery() -> tensor (generates a revised grasp motion), robot1_error_router_reinforce(tensor) -> None (updates the router using a loss tensor), robot1_unhandlable_error() -> str (reports a fatal fault). Recover the grasp and reinforce the router using the slip error tensor.",
