  {
    "instruction": "A sorting robot could not distinguish between an apple and a tomato because their appearance was too similar. Use the xxGemma DSL. First import tensor and robot1. Available functions: robot1_scan() -> tensor (captures image data), robot1_model(tensor) -> tensor (performs object recognition), robot1_act(tensor) -> str (executes the sorting action), robot1_error_router_determine() -> str (selects a recovery strategy), robot1_recognition_error_recovery() -> tensor (performs an additional recognition action), robot1_error_router_reinforce(tensor) -> None (updates the router), robot1_unhandlable_error() -> str (reports a fatal error). Recover by rescanning the object from another viewpoint without reinforcement. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}",
