    "instruction": "Two cooperative robots carrying a precision instrument detected that their motion synchronization drifted by several milliseconds. Use the xxGemma DSL. First import tensor and robot1. Available functions: robot1_scan() -> tensor (captures cooperative synchronization status), robot1_model(tensor) -> tensor (generates a cooperative control plan), robot1_act(tensor) -> str (executes the cooperative motion), robot1_error_router_determine() -> str (selects the recovery strategy), robot1_cooperation_error_recovery() -> tensor (generates a synchronization recovery action), robot1_error_router_reinforce(tensor) -> None (updates the router using a synchronization error tensor), robot1_unhandlable_error() -> str (reports a fatal error). Reset the synchronization timing and reinforce the router using the measured synchronization error tensor. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}",
    "dsl_program": "[CODE]import tensor\n[CODE]import robot1\n[CODE]$coop = tensor robot1_scan()\n[CODE]$plan = tensor robot1_model($coop)\n[CODE]robot1_act($plan)\n[EXCEPTION]robot1_exception: Synchronization drift detected.\n[COMMENT]Reset the synchronization timing and adapt the router using the synchronization error.\n[CODE]show robot1_error_router_determine()\n[RESULT]sync_reset\n[CODE]$loss = tensor robot1_cooperation_error_recovery()\n[CODE]robot1_error_router_reinforce($loss)\nThe robots restored synchronized motion and safely continued carrying the precision instrument.\n[CODE]return \"Recovered\"",
